-- Qualcomm buys back 29 million shares in July, August
-- 
-- Mon Aug 27, 2007 9:42am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/27/us-qualcomm-buyback-idUSWNAS292320070827

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Qualcomm Inc ( QCOM.O ) said on Monday that it bought back and retired about 29 million shares in July and August for about $1.1 billion under its $3 billion stock buyback program. 

 Qualcomm said it still has authorization to buy another $1.5 billion worth of its shares under the stock repurchase program announced May 22. It said it has bought back about 101 million shares for a value of $4 billion since its fiscal year 2003. (Reporting by  Sinead Carew )